# .component.tsx contract

A component file may contain ONLY:
1. Imports
2. One arrow-function component
3. Destructuring of props and of **one** call to its own `useComponentName` hook (or a single context consumer hook)
4. JSX

Anything else must be moved:

| Found in a component file | Move it to |
|---|---|
| `useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, `useCallback`, `useMemo`, `useReducer` | `useComponentName.hook.ts` |
| `type` declarations | `ComponentName.types.ts` |
| Top-level non-component `const` values | `ComponentName.constants.ts` |
| Pure functions (no JSX) | `./utils/<name>/<name>.util.ts` |
| JSX in a variable, or conditional JSX > ~5 lines | `./atoms/` or `./molecules/` child component |

Size limit: **150 lines** max. Decompose before finishing.

## One hook per component — not one hook for the whole tree

`useComponentName` serves **this component only**. It does not exist to gather all state for children.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — parent gathers everything; children are prop pipes
export const PageContentV2 = () => {
  const { mapCenter, sheetRef, cities, openSheet, selectedPlace, ...20 more } = usePageContentV2();
  return (
    <>
      <MapLayer center={mapCenter} ... />
      <Header onFocus={openSheet} ... />
      <BottomSheet sheetRef={sheetRef} cities={cities} ... />
    </>
  );
};

// ✅ GOOD — parent is layout; each child calls its own hook
export const PageContentV2 = () => {
  const { mountContainerRef } = usePageContentV2Mount();
  return (
    <PageContentV2Provider>
      <div ref={mountContainerRef}>
        <V2MapLayer />
        <V2Header />
        <V2BottomSheet />
        <V2PlaceOverlay />
      </div>
    </PageContentV2Provider>
  );
};

// ✅ GOOD — child owns its logic
export const V2MapLayer = () => {
  const { center, zoom, places, onPlaceClick, ... } = useV2MapLayer();
  return <MapView center={center} zoom={zoom} places={places} onPlaceClick={onPlaceClick} />;
};
```

**Red flags:** destructuring **10+ values** from one hook; passing **5+ props** that are really "business logic" into a child that has no hook of its own.

## Leaf example

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — CityList.component.tsx
export const CityList = ({ cities }: CityListProps) => {
  const { filteredCities, query, onQueryChange } = useCityList({ cities });
  return <div>{/* JSX only */}</div>;
};
```

## Memoization

Do not add `useMemo`, `useCallback`, or `memo` by default (especially not for booleans or other cheap values). See `memoization.mdc`. Logic that needs memoization belongs in the co-located hook, not the component file.

## Conditional JSX

Optional UI uses `&&`, never `? … : null`. See `jsx-conditional-rendering.mdc`.


```tsx
// ❌ BAD
{isMine ? <Button /> : null}

// ✅ GOOD
{isMine && <Button />}
```

## Self-check before finishing

- [ ] No React state/effect/memo hooks imported
- [ ] No inline `type`s, utils, or magic numbers
- [ ] Under 150 lines
- [ ] Data/handlers from **this** component's hook (or context), not a parent's god hook passed as props
- [ ] Feature page roots are layout shells — see `feature-composition.mdc`
- [ ] Optional JSX uses `&&`, not `? … : null`
- [ ] No unnecessary `useMemo` / `useCallback` / `memo` (see `memoization.mdc`)

